{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d6058aec-94c2-451b-91b0-b1d39d71f3cc","content":"The directory is empty — there are no existing files. Since this is a guidance/conversion request rather than an existing codebase task, here's exactly what to do:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nOn your `ContentPage` root element (or any element that sets `BindingContext`), add:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — this tells the XAML compiler the type of the binding source so it can **resolve every `{Binding …}` at compile time**.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** (not warnings) when a property name is misspelled or the type is wrong. To make sure you're getting them:\n\n| Setting | Why |\n|---|---|\n| `x:DataType` on the root element | Enables compiled bindings for the entire page |\n| **`$(MauiStrictXamlCompilation)`** in your `.csproj` | Optional — treats XAML warnings as errors |\n\nAdd to your `.csproj` if you want strict enforcement:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Quick rules\n\n- **Every `{Binding}` under an `x:DataType` scope is compiled.** A typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a build error.\n- If you need to opt out for one binding (e.g., a runtime-only context), use `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element to revert to reflection-based binding.\n- `x:DataType` is inherited — child elements use the nearest ancestor's type.\n\nThat's it. No other code changes needed; your existing `BindingContext = new SettingsViewModel()` in code-behind stays the same.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"990df8dc-9d74-4765-be3b-9e6a9a1491ef","outputTokens":747},"id":"a541ae5f-26ee-4f52-83b1-7d15b91d19b5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:24:26.248Z","parentId":"6d3a7ce1-28a7-4210-aa59-279bbcf304f3"}
